The purposes of the Kentucky Commercialization Fund Program are to:
Accelerate knowledge transfer and technological innovation, improve economic competitiveness, and spur economic growth in Kentucky-based companies;
Provide seed funding for promising technologies developed in Kentucky's colleges and universities;
Support promising technologies with commercial potential that are in their early stages of development;
Promote technologies and resources offered by Kentucky's postsecondary institutions to private enterprises; and
Support the formation and organization of private enterprise that advances commercial applications based on a university's research and development work.
